fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "releases/0-93.html#page-description", "fragment": "The Pitivi team is proud to announce the third release of the new version of Pitivi based on GES the GStreamer Editing Services library. This is a incremental bugfixing release so please make sure to see the and release notes to get the full picture. \nThis is now considered a beta release. As per the feedback we ve received since and the many fixes we ve made since then we are confident that the new release series is of much higher quality than the series and older. \nThis release works well for us and we make nice movies with it. Try it out have fun and report detailed bugs for issues you may encounter \nExecutive summary \nSee the list of reported bugs that have been resolved in \nSince the release commits were made across files. Here is a summary of some noteworthy commits \nf5d7a3 timeline Fix dragging an asset to the ruler bbff99d project Default to a square pixel aspect ratio d514 clipmediaprops Prevent setting an invalid framerate from a misdetected clip ca7dd0 mainwindow Actually use DAR not PAR to set the viewer s display aspect ratio project Emit rendering settings changed when the pixel aspect ratio changes b272f07 project Flush the pipeline when we set restriction caps fee0c viewer Add a button to undock the viewer directly instead of using menu actions db7e clipmediaprops Allow closing the dialog with ESC ab268 Show the full pathname in the tooltip for an asset d95 elements Fix lines appearing a bit to the left ff3bae elements Make sure the line remains straight when adding a keyframe when clicked a71127 mainwindow Allow pressing ESC or q to close the preview asset window dfc908c tests Skip TestGnomeSystem.testPowerInhibition if the power is inhibited ffd50e timeline Handle only the key press release events on the timeline elements Fix video clips keyframes and lines vertical position e54f0f5 clipproperties Fix effect selection in the clip properties tab d3268b mainwindo